From triangle \( P Q C \), we obtain
\[
\begin{array}{r}
x^{2}=(t-4)^{2}-16 \\
x^{2}=t^{2}-8 t \Rightarrow x=\sqrt{t^{2}-8 t}
\end{array}
\]

From triangle \( A B C \), we obtain
\[
\begin{array}{l}
(x+r)^{2}=t^{2}+r^{2} \\
x^{2}+2 x r+r^{2}=t^{2}+r^{2} \\
\Rightarrow x^{2}+2 x r=t^{2}
\end{array}
\]

Substituting equation 1 into equation 2, we get
\[
r^{2}=\frac{16 t}{t-8}
\]

The volume of the cone is
\[
\begin{array}{c}
V=\frac{1}{3} \pi r^{2} t \\
V=\frac{1}{3} \pi\left(\frac{16 t^{2}}{t-8}\right)
\end{array}
\]

The condition for the minimum volume is \( V^{\prime}=0 \)
\[
\begin{array}{l}
V^{\prime}=\frac{1}{3} \pi\left(\frac{32 t(t-8)-16 t^{2}}{(t-8)^{2}}\right)=0 \\
t^{2}-16 t=0 \\
t=0 \text { or } t=16
\end{array}
\]

