A bag of feed will be finished in 12 days if provided to fish A. This gives us the eating rate of fish A, \( V_{A}=\frac{\text { bag }}{12} \). On the other hand, if the same bag of feed is given to fish B, it will be consumed in 6 days. This gives us the eating rate of fish B, \( V_{B}=\frac{\text { bag }}{6} \).

If the bag of feed is provided to both fish A and B, the time it will take for them to finish it can be determined with the combined eating rate \( V_{\mathrm{comb}}=V_{A}+V_{B}=\frac{\text { bag }}{12}+\frac{\text { bag }}{6} \). The eating time is calculated as follows:
\[
\begin{aligned}
T & =\frac{\text { bag }}{V_{\mathrm{comb}}}=\frac{\text { bag }}{\frac{\text { bag }}{12}+\frac{\text { bag }}{6}}=\frac{1}{\frac{1}{12}+\frac{1}{6}} \\
& =\frac{1}{\frac{3}{12}}=\frac{12}{3}=4 \text { days }
\end{aligned}
\]

